===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ぜんまい|alt=紫萁:uncommon,狗脊:rare}}
{{wp|ja:ゼンマイ}}
{{wp|Osmunda japonica}}
[[File:Osmunda japonica 002.jpg|thumb|250px|{{m|ja|薇|tr=zenmai}}: a coiled [[fiddlehead]] [[frond]] of the '''{{vern|Japanese flowering fern}}'''.]]

Uncertain. Theories include:
* Shift from {{m|ja|[[銭]][[舞]]|tr=zeni mai|lit=[[coin]] + [[twirling]] / [[spinning]]}}, from the way the [[fiddlehead]]s look like rotating or twirling coins
* Shift from {{m|ja|[[銭]][[巻き]]|tr=zeni maki|lit=[[coin]] + [[roll]]}}, from the way the coil of a [[fiddlehead]] with the hole in the center looks like a traditional coin (which also has a hole in the center)<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>
* Shift from {{m|ja|[[千]][[巻き]]|tr=sen maki|lit=[[thousand]] + [[roll]]}}, from the way the repeating pattern of the [[fiddlehead]]s look like a lot of small things in a roll

The "roll" derivation would align with the derivation of synonym {{m|ja|巻子|tr=makago}}.

First attested in 1709.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|薇・紫萁・狗脊}}</ref>

